(26, 'Okpalaugo', 'Okpalaugo.chukwuka1@gmail.com', 'EPL: What Guardiola said after Man City failed to beat Newcastle United', '<p>Manchester City boss, Pep Guardiola has disclosed that his side must &ldquo;accept, to work on their strengths and learn from it&rdquo; following their 2-2 draw against Newcastle United in the Premier League on Saturday</p>\r\n<p>Goals from Raheem Sterling, Jetro Willems, Kevin De Bruyne and Jonjo Shelvey ensure both teams got a point each at St. James&rsquo; Park.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;It&rsquo;s what we&rsquo;ve lived the last four years. We found a way and today, we found it again but unfortunately, at the end, we conceded a goal,&rdquo; Guardiola told reporters at his post-match press conference after the game.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;We could not score all the chances we had; they scored the two chances they had.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;We have to accept it, work on strengths and learn from it.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;It&rsquo;s tough but we have just two days to recover.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;In good moments, be calm. In bad moments, live these kind of moments.&rdquo;</p>', '1575137065_thump.jpg', '2019-11-30 18:05:52', 1),
