(1, 'Questions and Answers to last week quiz', '<p><strong>English</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>1.&nbsp;</strong>Bolt from blue</p>\r\n<p>a. Thundering</p>\r\n<p>b. A Complete Surprise</p>\r\n<p>c. Inform something bad</p>\r\n<p>d. No idea</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: b</p>\r\n<p><strong>2</strong><strong>.</strong>When the principal entered the class, a student..........on the blackboard.</p>\r\n<p>a. wrote</p>\r\n<p>b. Was writting</p>\r\n<p>c. Writes</p>\r\n<p>d. is writing</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: b</p>\r\n<p><strong>3.</strong>&nbsp;find the correctly spelt word</p>\r\n<p>a. Reannaisance&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>b. Renaissance.</p>\r\n<p>c. Rennaissance&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>d. Renaisance&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: b</p>\r\n<p><strong>4.&nbsp;</strong>Select Correct word</p>\r\n<p>a. Aceleration&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>b. Aceeleration&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>c. Accelelation&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>d. Acceleration</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: d</p>\r\n<p><strong>5.</strong>Select correct word</p>\r\n<p>a. Agressive&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>b. Agrressive&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>c. Aggressive</p>\r\n<p>d. Aggresive&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: c</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>CURRENTS AFFAIRS</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>1.&nbsp;</strong>what was the first party in Nigeria</p>\r\n<p>a. PDP</p>\r\n<p>b. APC</p>\r\n<p>c. NNDP</p>\r\n<p>d. NAPD</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: c</p>\r\n<p><strong>2.</strong> What does the eagle in Nigeria coat of arm represent?</p>\r\n<p>a. Strength</p>\r\n<p>b. Unity</p>\r\n<p>c. Peace</p>\r\n<p>d. Power</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: a</p>\r\n<p><strong>3.</strong> what was the first capital city in Nigeria?</p>\r\n<p>a. Calabar</p>\r\n<p>b. Ikeja</p>\r\n<p>c. Abuja</p>\r\n<p>d. Kano</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: a</p>\r\n<p><strong>4.&nbsp;</strong>who designed the Nigerian flag.</p>\r\n<p>a. Michael Yakubu</p>\r\n<p>b. Michael Taiwo Akinkumi</p>\r\n<p>c. Akinkumi Omoniyi</p>\r\n<p>d. John Obi</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: b</p>\r\n<p><strong>5.&nbsp;</strong>When was Nigeria formed?</p>\r\n<p>a. 1915</p>\r\n<p>b. 1916</p>\r\n<p>c.1914</p>\r\n<p>d. 1924</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: c</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>MATHEMATICS</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>1.</strong>If algebraic expression is [4(a+2b-3c)-3(2b-3c)]+2a then answer will be.</p>\r\n<p>A. 7a-3b+4c</p>\r\n<p>B. 6a+2b-3c</p>\r\n<p>C. 8a+3b-4c</p>\r\n<p>D. 9a+2b+5c</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: B</p>\r\n<p><strong>2.&nbsp;</strong>By solving expression 4[3s-2(6s-8)], answer will be</p>\r\n<p>A. 12s-16</p>\r\n<p>B. 12s-16</p>\r\n<p>C. 12s+16</p>\r\n<p>D. 16s+12</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: C</p>\r\n<p><strong>3.&nbsp;</strong>On evaluating expression 10(x-20y)+100x, answer will be</p>\r\n<p>A. 100x+240y</p>\r\n<p>B. 110x+200y</p>\r\n<p>C. 200x-110y</p>\r\n<p>D. 110x-200y</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: D</p>\r\n<p><strong>4.&nbsp;</strong>Joseph has 10 candies. He gave 4 candies to John and John returned 2 candies to Joseph after few days. Number of candies Joseph has altogether are</p>\r\n<p>A. 8</p>\r\n<p>B. -8</p>\r\n<p>C. 10</p>\r\n<p>D. -10</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: A</p>\r\n<p><strong>5.&nbsp;</strong>Sum of -4,-6,-8 and 8 is</p>\r\n<p>A. -14</p>\r\n<p>B. -12</p>\r\n<p>C. 14</p>\r\n<p>D. -10</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: D</p>\r\n<p><strong>6.&nbsp;</strong>Ana has 4 stamps. She bought 8 stamps more and Mary borrowed two stamps from Ana. Total number of stamps Ana have are</p>\r\n<p>A. -12</p>\r\n<p>B. 12</p>\r\n<p>C. 10</p>\r\n<p>D. 8</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: C</p>\r\n<p><strong>7.</strong>Sum of 5x+3y and 4x-2y is</p>\r\n<p>A. 5x-8y</p>\r\n<p>B. 9x+y</p>\r\n<p>C. 8x+4y</p>\r\n<p>D. 6x+5y</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: B</p>\r\n<p><strong>8.&nbsp;</strong>If expression 4c+2b+4d is subtracted from 3c+4b+5d then answer will be</p>\r\n<p>A. -c+d</p>\r\n<p>B. c+d</p>\r\n<p>C. 2c-4d</p>\r\n<p>D. 3c+2b-5d</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: A</p>\r\n<p><strong>9.&nbsp;</strong>If you subtract 50 from -30 then answer will be</p>\r\n<p>A. 40</p>\r\n<p>B. 60</p>\r\n<p>C. -80</p>\r\n<p>D. 90</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: C</p>\r\n<p><strong>10.&nbsp;</strong>60/3 is</p>\r\n<p>A. 20</p>\r\n<p>B. 30</p>\r\n<p>C. 40</p>\r\n<p>D. 15</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: A</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>BASIC COMPUTER</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>1.&nbsp;</strong>who is the father of computer?</p>\r\n<p>A. Allen Tuning</p>\r\n<p>B. Charles Babbage</p>\r\n<p>C. Simur Cry</p>\r\n<p>D. Augusta Adaming</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: B</p>\r\n<p><strong>2.&nbsp;</strong>ALU is</p>\r\n<p>A. Arithmetic Logic Unit</p>\r\n<p>B. Array Logic Unit</p>\r\n<p>C. Application Logic Unit</p>\r\n<p>D. None of the above</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: A</p>\r\n<p><strong>3.</strong> WAN stands for</p>\r\n<p>A. WAP Area Network</p>\r\n<p>B. Wide Area Network</p>\r\n<p>C. Wide Array Network</p>\r\n<p>D. Wireless Area Network</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: B</p>\r\n<p><strong>4.&nbsp;</strong>who is the chief of Microsoft?</p>\r\n<p>A. Babbage</p>\r\n<p>B. Bill Gates</p>\r\n<p>C. Bill Clinton</p>\r\n<p>D. None of these</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: B</p>\r\n<p><strong>5.&nbsp;</strong>BIOS stands for?</p>\r\n<p>A. Basic Input Output System</p>\r\n<p>B. Binary Input Output System</p>\r\n<p>C. Basic Input Off System</p>\r\n<p>D. All of the Above</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: D</p>\r\n<p><strong>6.&nbsp;</strong>An area of a computer that temporarily holds data waiting to be processed is?</p>\r\n<p>A. CPU</p>\r\n<p>B. memory</p>\r\n<p>C. Storage</p>\r\n<p>D. File</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: B</p>\r\n<p><strong>7.&nbsp;</strong>The key used to run the selected command is?</p>\r\n<p>A. SHIFT</p>\r\n<p>B. TAB</p>\r\n<p>C.ENTER</p>\r\n<p>D. CTRL</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: C</p>\r\n<p><strong>8.</strong> Which of the following is the smallest storage</p>\r\n<p>A. Megabyte</p>\r\n<p>B. Gigabyte</p>\r\n<p>C.Terabyte</p>\r\n<p>D. None of the above.</p>\r\n<p>Correct answer: D</p>\r\n<p><strong>9.</strong> Touch screen is</p>\r\n<p>A. Input device</p>\r\n<p>B. Output device</p>\r\n<p>C. Both A &amp; B above</p>\r\n<p>D. None of the above</p>\r\n<p>CorrectAnswer: C</p>\r\n<p><strong>10.&nbsp;</strong>To prevent the loss of data during power failures, we use a(an)</p>\r\n<p>A. Encryption Program</p>\r\n<p>B. Surge Protector</p>\r\n<p>C. Firewall</p>\r\n<p>D. UPS</p>\r\n<p>Correctanswer: D</p>', '2019-10-29 07:37:57'),
(3, 'Registration for upcoming free airtime quiz have started.', '<p>Registration for upcoming free airtime quiz started yesterday.</p>\r\n<p>The date for the quiz might change due to technical issues.</p>\r\n<p>Hurry up and register, registration is free.</p>', '2019-10-28 23:57:34'),
(4, 'Subjects for upcoming free airtime quiz are:', '<p>Below are the subjects for upcoming free airtime quiz:</p>\r\n<p>1. English</p>\r\n<p>2. Basic Mathematics</p>\r\n<p>3. Basic Computer</p>\r\n<p>4. Currents affairs</p>', '2019-10-29 00:01:04'),
(5, 'Update on today\'s quiz', '<p>Due to some technical issue, the free airtime quiz will not hold today. Out team is working on resolving the issue.</p>\r\n<p>Mean while a lot of people are registering double account.</p>\r\n<p>Be warned!!</p>\r\n<p>Once anybody that emerged as the winner of the quiz was found with double account, he/she will be deleted from the system and the person next to him or her will come up and take the position&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The quiz will hold next week Saturday 9/11/2019</p>\r\n<p>Keep inviting your friends to register for the quiz.</p>', '2019-11-02 17:46:32'),
(6, 'Instructions on tomorrow upcoming quiz', '<p>1. Make sure you are not found with double account, if found with double account will be denied the airtime</p>\r\n<p>2. Read the questions carefully before clicking on the answer. Because there is no provision to go back and make changes to previous answered questions.</p>\r\n<p>3. &nbsp;NOTE! &nbsp;The sign ^ means raised to power.</p>\r\n<p>4. You can click on rank to see your position or history to see your performance</p>\r\n<p>5. Don\'t try opening another browser tab. If you do so the questions will automatically submit.</p>\r\n<p>6. Use Chrome brower or Mozilla Firefox.</p>\r\n<p>7. You can login any time tomorrow to answer thequestions</p>\r\n<p>8. <em>At the end of tomorrow, the top three winners will get the airtime directly recharged to the number they registered with.</em></p>', '2019-11-08 12:23:08'),
(7, 'Last week quiz questions and answers', '<p>BASIC COMPUTER</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;1. You organize files by sorting them in&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A. Archives</p>\r\n<p>B. Folders</p>\r\n<p>C. Indexes</p>\r\n<p>D. Lists</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>2. Junk e-mail is also called</p>\r\n<p>A.Spam</p>\r\n<p>B. Spoof</p>\r\n<p>C. Sniffer Script</p>\r\n<p>D. Spool</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>3. Which of the following is not anti-viruses software?</p>\r\n<p>A. NAV</p>\r\n<p>B. F-Prot</p>\r\n<p>C. Oracle</p>\r\n<p>D. McAFee</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>4. EEPROM Stands for?</p>\r\n<p>A. Electrically Erasable Programmable Read Only Memory</p>\r\n<p>B. Easily Erasable Programmable Read only Memory.</p>\r\n<p>C. Electronic Erasable Programmable Read only memory</p>\r\n<p>D. None of the above</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>5. Which of the following are the functions of operating system?</p>\r\n<p>A. Allocates resources</p>\r\n<p>B. Monitors Activities</p>\r\n<p>C. Manages disks and files</p>\r\n<p>D. All of the above</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>6. Which of the following is Not one of the four major data processing functions of a computer</p>\r\n<p>A. Gathering data</p>\r\n<p>B. Processing data into information</p>\r\n<p>C. Analyzing the data or information</p>\r\n<p>D. Storing the data or information</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>7. The CPU and memory are located on the &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.</p>\r\n<p>A. Expansion board</p>\r\n<p>B. Motherboard</p>\r\n<p>C. Storage device</p>\r\n<p>D. Output Drives.</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>8. The process of transferring files from a computer on the internet to your computer is called?</p>\r\n<p>A. Downloading</p>\r\n<p>B. Uploading</p>\r\n<p>C. FTP</p>\r\n<p>D. JPEG</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>9. Which of the following is not a binary number?</p>\r\n<p>A. 001</p>\r\n<p>B. 101</p>\r\n<p>C. 202</p>\r\n<p>D. 110</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>10. A modem is connected to &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.</p>\r\n<p>A. A telephone Line</p>\r\n<p>B. A Keyboard</p>\r\n<p>C. A Printer</p>\r\n<p>D. A Monitor</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>ENGLISH</p>\r\n<p>1. Does&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;Know that &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; was absent?</p>\r\n<p>A. She, me</p>\r\n<p>B. She, I</p>\r\n<p>C. Her, me</p>\r\n<p>D. Her, I</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>2. Please tell&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.., &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. have obtained a degree in chemistry.</p>\r\n<p>A. He, I</p>\r\n<p>B. Him, me</p>\r\n<p>C. Him, I</p>\r\n<p>D. He, me</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>3. I remember that&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.bought the fruits from&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.</p>\r\n<p>A. They, we</p>\r\n<p>B. Them, us</p>\r\n<p>C. Them, we</p>\r\n<p>D. They, us</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>4. Fate smiles&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..those who untiringly grapple with stark realities of life.</p>\r\n<p>A. with</p>\r\n<p>B. over</p>\r\n<p>C. on</p>\r\n<p>D. round</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>5. The miser gazed&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;at the pile of gold coins in front of him</p>\r\n<p>A. Avidly</p>\r\n<p>B. Admiringly</p>\r\n<p>C. Thoughtfully</p>\r\n<p>D. Earnestly</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>6. Catching the earlier train will give us the &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;. To do some shopping.</p>\r\n<p>A. chance</p>\r\n<p>B. luck</p>\r\n<p>C. possibility</p>\r\n<p>D. occasion</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>7. He said to interviewer, &ldquo;Could you please repeat the question?&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>A. He requested the interviewer if he could please repeat the question.</p>\r\n<p>B. He requested the interviewer to please repeat the question.</p>\r\n<p>C. He requested the interviewer to repeat the question.</p>\r\n<p>D. He requested the interviewer if he could repeat the question.</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>8. Choose the word which is most similar in meaning to CLAMORED</p>\r\n<p>A. Acclaimed</p>\r\n<p>B. Applauded</p>\r\n<p>C. Cried</p>\r\n<p>D. Decided</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>9. Choose the word which is most opposite in meaning of VIABLE</p>\r\n<p>A. Practicable</p>\r\n<p>B. Reasonable</p>\r\n<p>C. Feasible</p>\r\n<p>D. Impossible</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>10. Choose the option with grammatical or Idiomatic error in it</p>\r\n<p>A. The CBI has filled a petition in NIA court</p>\r\n<p>B. Here seaking its permission to interrogate</p>\r\n<p>C. A sri Lankan national held for</p>\r\n<p>D. No error</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>BASIC MATHEMATICS</p>\r\n<p>1.&nbsp; The square root of 0.0081 is &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..</p>\r\n<p>A. 0.09</p>\r\n<p>B. 0.9</p>\r\n<p>C. 0.91</p>\r\n<p>D. 0.009</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>2. 10^-3 means &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.</p>\r\n<p>A. milli</p>\r\n<p>B. centi</p>\r\n<p>C. micro</p>\r\n<p>D. deci</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>3. 142x16= &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;</p>\r\n<p>A. 7222</p>\r\n<p>B. 2227</p>\r\n<p>C. 2722</p>\r\n<p>D. 2272</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>4. 1^0 is equal to &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;</p>\r\n<p>A. -1</p>\r\n<p>B. 0</p>\r\n<p>C. 1</p>\r\n<p>D. None of these</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>5. 4505/5 = &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.</p>\r\n<p>A. 901</p>\r\n<p>B. 910</p>\r\n<p>C. 190</p>\r\n<p>D. 109</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>6. 10003-999 = &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;</p>\r\n<p>A. 4009</p>\r\n<p>B. 9004</p>\r\n<p>C. 9040</p>\r\n<p>D. 9400</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>7. All natural numbers and 0 are called the &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; numbers.</p>\r\n<p>A. Whole</p>\r\n<p>B. Prime</p>\r\n<p>C. Integer</p>\r\n<p>D. Rational</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>8. The cube root of 1331 is &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.</p>\r\n<p>A. 11</p>\r\n<p>B. 13</p>\r\n<p>C. 18</p>\r\n<p>D. 15</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>9. How many digits are there in 1000?</p>\r\n<p>A. One digit.</p>\r\n<p>B. Two digits</p>\r\n<p>C. Three digits</p>\r\n<p>D. Four digits</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>10. Complete the sequence 13,16,&hellip;,22</p>\r\n<p>A. 17</p>\r\n<p>B. 18</p>\r\n<p>C. 19</p>\r\n<p>D. 20</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>CORRENTS AFFAIRS</p>\r\n<p>1. Between 1960 and 1966 Nigeria was governed under the&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A. Presidential System</p>\r\n<p>B. Westminster System</p>\r\n<p>C. Confederal System</p>\r\n<p>D. Unitary System</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>2. Which of the following political parties did not participate in the 1979 General Elections in Nigeria?</p>\r\n<p>A. Unity Party of Nigeria</p>\r\n<p>B. National Party of Nigeria</p>\r\n<p>C. Social Democratic Party</p>\r\n<p>D. NNDP</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>3. Which of the following courts served as the highest judicial organ for Nigeria up till 1963?</p>\r\n<p>A. Supreme Court</p>\r\n<p>B. Federal Court of Appeal</p>\r\n<p>C. Appellate Court</p>\r\n<p>D. The Privy Council.</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>4. Which of these men introduced indirect rule in Nigeria?</p>\r\n<p>A. Mungo Park</p>\r\n<p>B. Dr. Nnamdi Azikiwe</p>\r\n<p>C. Lord Lugard</p>\r\n<p>D. Sir James Rovertson.</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>5. Polities is an act for</p>\r\n<p>A. Man to govern himself</p>\r\n<p>B. Man to create government</p>\r\n<p>C. States to control its destiny</p>\r\n<p>D. Man to determine others</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2019-11-16 18:21:21'),
(8, 'Instructions on Tomorrows(23/11/2019) quiz', '<p>1. There will be four sessions;</p>\r\n<p>i. English</p>\r\n<p>ii. Basic Maths</p>\r\n<p>iII. Basic Computer</p>\r\n<p>iv. Currents affairs</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>2. Read the questions carefully before choosing your option.</p>\r\n<p>3. Steps to answer the quiz:</p>\r\n<p>i. Enter egeniusquiz.com scroll down and click on start quiz(you will be able to see the start quiz link tomorrow) in the yellow box</p>\r\n<p>ii. While in the quiz page, To view the start button, slide right or left.</p>\r\n<p>4. Use chrome, Uc browser, or mozzila firefox browser for the quiz.</p>\r\n<p>The first 3 positions gets airtime latest Sunday morning.</p>\r\n<p>Goodluck!!!</p>\r\n<p>For morw details Contact us on:</p>\r\n<p>Email: egeniusquiz@egeniusquiz.com</p>\r\n<p>WhatsApp: +2348037869935</p>\r\n<p>Facebook: Facebook.com/egeniusquiz</p>\r\n<p>Twitter: twitter.com/egeniusquiz</p>', '2019-11-22 13:46:22'),
(9, 'Last week quiz questions and answers', '<p>Basic Mathematics</p>\r\n<p>1. What is the largest two digits prime number?</p>\r\n<p>A. 96</p>\r\n<p>B. 97</p>\r\n<p>C. 98</p>\r\n<p>D. 99</p>\r\n<p>2. Correct Answer [B]</p>\r\n<p>1 dime = &hellip;&hellip;..dollar</p>\r\n<p>A. 0.20</p>\r\n<p>B. 10</p>\r\n<p>C. 0.10</p>\r\n<p>D. 0.01</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [C]</p>\r\n<p>3. How many factors are there in 71?</p>\r\n<p>A. 1</p>\r\n<p>B. 2</p>\r\n<p>C. 3</p>\r\n<p>D. None of the above.</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [B]</p>\r\n<p>4. What is the largest number in 15/17, 15/18, 15/19, 15/21</p>\r\n<p>A. 15/17</p>\r\n<p>B. 15/18</p>\r\n<p>C. 15/19</p>\r\n<p>D. 15/21</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [A]</p>\r\n<p>5. What is the average value of 25,20, 23, and 22?</p>\r\n<p>A. 20</p>\r\n<p>B. 21.5</p>\r\n<p>C. 22.5</p>\r\n<p>D. 24</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [C]</p>\r\n<p>6. 2 is a &hellip;&hellip;&hellip; number</p>\r\n<p>A. Odd</p>\r\n<p>B. Prime</p>\r\n<p>C. Composite</p>\r\n<p>D. None of these</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [B]</p>\r\n<p>7. What is the sum of one digit prime number</p>\r\n<p>A. 11</p>\r\n<p>B. 13</p>\r\n<p>C. 15</p>\r\n<p>D. 17</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [D]</p>\r\n<p>8. How many hours in 90 minutes?</p>\r\n<p>A. 1.5 hours</p>\r\n<p>B. 1.30 hours</p>\r\n<p>C. 1 hour</p>\r\n<p>D. None of these</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [A]</p>\r\n<p>9. Subtract 457 from 832</p>\r\n<p>A. 375</p>\r\n<p>B. 57</p>\r\n<p>C. 376</p>\r\n<p>D. 970</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [A]</p>\r\n<p>10. 50 times 5 is equal to</p>\r\n<p>A. 2500</p>\r\n<p>B. 505</p>\r\n<p>C. 500</p>\r\n<p>D. None of these</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [D]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Basic Computer</p>\r\n<p>1. Human beings are referred to as homosapinens, which device is called sillico sapiens?</p>\r\n<p>A. Monitor</p>\r\n<p>B. Hardware</p>\r\n<p>C. Robot</p>\r\n<p>D. Computer</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [D]</p>\r\n<p>2. DOS stands for</p>\r\n<p>A. Disk Operating System</p>\r\n<p>B. Disk Operating Session</p>\r\n<p>C. Digital Operating System</p>\r\n<p>D. Digital Open System</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [A]</p>\r\n<p>3. 1 Byte = ?</p>\r\n<p>A. 8 bits</p>\r\n<p>B. 4 bits</p>\r\n<p>C. 2 bits</p>\r\n<p>D. 9 bits</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [A]</p>\r\n<p>4. &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;. Is the key to close a selected drop-down list; calcel a command and close a dialog box</p>\r\n<p>A. TAB</p>\r\n<p>B. SHIFT</p>\r\n<p>C. ESC</p>\r\n<p>D. FIO</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [C]</p>\r\n<p>5. Data becomes&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. when it is presented in a format that people can understand</p>\r\n<p>A. Processed</p>\r\n<p>B. Graphs</p>\r\n<p>C. Information</p>\r\n<p>D. Presentation</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [C]</p>\r\n<p>6. The term &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; designates equipment&rsquo;s that might be added to a computer system to enhance its functionality.</p>\r\n<p>A. Digital device</p>\r\n<p>B. System add-on</p>\r\n<p>C. Disk pack</p>\r\n<p>D. Peripheral device</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [D]</p>\r\n<p>7. To move a copy of file from one computer to another over a communication channel is called?</p>\r\n<p>A. File transfer</p>\r\n<p>B. File encryption</p>\r\n<p>C. File modification</p>\r\n<p>D. File copying</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [A]</p>\r\n<p>8. What kind of memory is both static and non-volatile?</p>\r\n<p>A. RAM</p>\r\n<p>B. ROM</p>\r\n<p>C. BIOS</p>\r\n<p>D. CACHE</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [B]</p>\r\n<p>9. The task of performing operations like arithmetic and logical operations is called</p>\r\n<p>A. Processing</p>\r\n<p>B. Storing</p>\r\n<p>C. Editing</p>\r\n<p>D. Sorting</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [A]</p>\r\n<p>10. Servers are computers that provide resources to other computers connected to a &hellip;&hellip;..</p>\r\n<p>A. Networked</p>\r\n<p>B. Mainframe</p>\r\n<p>C. Super computer</p>\r\n<p>D. Client.</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [B]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>English</p>\r\n<p>1. When the doctor &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;, the patient was already &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..</p>\r\n<p>A. Arrived; died</p>\r\n<p>B. Arrived; dead</p>\r\n<p>C. Arrive; dead</p>\r\n<p>D. Arriving; dying.</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [B]</p>\r\n<p>2. Age and experience &hellip;&hellip;&hellip; wisdom to man</p>\r\n<p>A. Bing</p>\r\n<p>B. Have brought</p>\r\n<p>C. Are bringing</p>\r\n<p>D. Brings</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [D]</p>\r\n<p>3. He was accused of bringing money into the country in &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. of foreign exchange rules.</p>\r\n<p>A. Anticipation</p>\r\n<p>B. Compensation</p>\r\n<p>C. Perpetration</p>\r\n<p>D. Violation</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [D]</p>\r\n<p>4. The country&rsquo;s economic growth was adversely &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;. By political instability</p>\r\n<p>A. Reflected</p>\r\n<p>B. Effected</p>\r\n<p>C. Affected</p>\r\n<p>D. Expected.</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [C]</p>\r\n<p>5. Choose&nbsp; the one which best expresses the meaning of MENACE</p>\r\n<p>A. Request</p>\r\n<p>B. Prayer</p>\r\n<p>C. Threat</p>\r\n<p>D. Curse</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [C]</p>\r\n<p>6. Choose the one which best expresses the meaning of CENSURE</p>\r\n<p>A. Criticize</p>\r\n<p>B. Appreciate</p>\r\n<p>C. Blame</p>\r\n<p>D. Abuse</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [A]</p>\r\n<p>7. Choose the one which best expresses the meaning of COLOSSAL</p>\r\n<p>A. Gigantic</p>\r\n<p>B. Colorful</p>\r\n<p>C. Beautiful</p>\r\n<p>D. Fantastic</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [A]</p>\r\n<p>8. Find correct spelt word.</p>\r\n<p>A. Compitation</p>\r\n<p>B. Fascination</p>\r\n<p>C. Assemilation&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>D. Vindicasion</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [B]</p>\r\n<p>9. Find correct spelt word</p>\r\n<p>A. Coherant</p>\r\n<p>B. Commendation</p>\r\n<p>C. Tomorow</p>\r\n<p>D. Advicable</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [B]</p>\r\n<p>10. Find correct spelt word.</p>\r\n<p>A. Preferennce</p>\r\n<p>B. Preferrence&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>C. Preference</p>\r\n<p>D. Prefference&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [C]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Currents Affairs</p>\r\n<p>1. The military coup of July, 1975 which topped general Yakubu Gowon from power took place when he was attending which important event?</p>\r\n<p>A. OAU summit in Kampala</p>\r\n<p>B. UN General Assembly in New York</p>\r\n<p>C. Assembly of Head of States of Ecowas in Monrovia&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>D. The Olympic Games</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [A]</p>\r\n<p>2. A parliamentary System, who ensure that members are in the house to vote on major issues</p>\r\n<p>A. Party leaders</p>\r\n<p>B. Speaker of the house</p>\r\n<p>C. Clerk of the house&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>D. Whip</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [D]</p>\r\n<p>3. Who is the current minister for labour?</p>\r\n<p>A. Dr. Ebele Ojukwu</p>\r\n<p>B. Dr. Chris Nwabueze Ngige</p>\r\n<p>C. Lai Mohammed</p>\r\n<p>D. Sunday Dare</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [B]</p>\r\n<p>4. Who is the minister of Education</p>\r\n<p>A. Adamu Adamu</p>\r\n<p>B. Richard Adeniyi Adebayo</p>\r\n<p>C. Ogbonnaya Onu</p>\r\n<p>D. Clement Agba</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [A]</p>\r\n<p>5. Who is the minister of Environment?</p>\r\n<p>A. Muhammad Mahmood</p>\r\n<p>B. Sirika Hudi</p>\r\n<p>C. Zabair Dada</p>\r\n<p>D. Adeleke Mamora</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer [A]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2019-11-27 14:36:32'),
