(13, 'Questions and answers to last week Saturday quiz', '<p>BASIC COMPUTER</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;1. Which of the following is not a famous operating system?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A. Window Vista</p>\r\n<p>B. Linus</p>\r\n<p>C. Sun OS</p>\r\n<p>D. Virtual Box</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>2. Computer Keyboard is an example of</p>\r\n<p>A. Input Device</p>\r\n<p>B. Output Device</p>\r\n<p>C. Input and Output</p>\r\n<p>D. None of these.</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>3. While sending an email, if an email address is put into &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. Field, the person will get a copy of the email but no other recipient will see the email address that was put in the above field</p>\r\n<p>A. Cc</p>\r\n<p>B. Bcc</p>\r\n<p>C. Junk</p>\r\n<p>D. Subject</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>4. &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; is an application program that allows teachers to present their lesson in more dynamic way than simply lecturing and writing on the blackboard.</p>\r\n<p>A. MS-Word</p>\r\n<p>B. MS-Excel</p>\r\n<p>C. MS-Power Point</p>\r\n<p>D. MS-Access</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>5. Laser printer is an example of</p>\r\n<p>A. Input</p>\r\n<p>B. Scanner</p>\r\n<p>C. Output</p>\r\n<p>D. None of these</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>6. Which of the following stores more data</p>\r\n<p>A. Floppy</p>\r\n<p>B. DVD</p>\r\n<p>C. CD</p>\r\n<p>D. None of these</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>7. LAT Stands for</p>\r\n<p>A. Large Area Transmission</p>\r\n<p>B. Local Area Transmission</p>\r\n<p>C. Local Area Transport</p>\r\n<p>D. None of the above</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>8. BCD Stands for</p>\r\n<p>A. Bits Coded Decimal</p>\r\n<p>B. Binary Coded Decimal</p>\r\n<p>C. Binary Coded Data</p>\r\n<p>D. Bytes Coded Decimal</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>9. Central Processing unit consists of</p>\r\n<p>A. Control Unit</p>\r\n<p>B. Arithmetic and logic Unit</p>\r\n<p>C. Registers</p>\r\n<p>D. All of these</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>10. Personal Computer can be connected together to form a</p>\r\n<p>A. Super Computer</p>\r\n<p>B. Server</p>\r\n<p>C. Enterprise</p>\r\n<p>D. Network</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>ENGLISH</p>\r\n<p>1. New York is &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; large city</p>\r\n<p>A. A</p>\r\n<p>B. An</p>\r\n<p>C. The</p>\r\n<p>D. None of these</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>2. Find out the adjective of SEASON</p>\r\n<p>A. Seasonal</p>\r\n<p>B. Seasoning</p>\r\n<p>C. Seasonable</p>\r\n<p>D. Seasoned</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>3. Find out the adjective of SLOW</p>\r\n<p>A. Slow</p>\r\n<p>B. Slowly</p>\r\n<p>C. Slowingly</p>\r\n<p>D. None of these</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>4. Select the odd one out</p>\r\n<p>A. Canteen</p>\r\n<p>B. Dancer</p>\r\n<p>C. Stage</p>\r\n<p>D. Makeup</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>5. Select the odd one out</p>\r\n<p>A. Blackboard</p>\r\n<p>B. Duster</p>\r\n<p>C. Computer</p>\r\n<p>D. Chalk</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>6. On seeing the police, the thief started &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.</p>\r\n<p>A. Run</p>\r\n<p>B. Runs</p>\r\n<p>C. Running</p>\r\n<p>D. Its running</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>7. The train is &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..out of the platform now.</p>\r\n<p>A. Pull</p>\r\n<p>B. Pulls</p>\r\n<p>C. Pulled</p>\r\n<p>D. Pulling</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>8. Select the proper suffix of &lsquo;Scholar&rsquo;</p>\r\n<p>A. er</p>\r\n<p>B. ty&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>C. hood</p>\r\n<p>D. ship</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>9. let us play</p>\r\n<p>A. Can we</p>\r\n<p>B. Do we?</p>\r\n<p>C. Shall we</p>\r\n<p>D. Shalln&rsquo;t we?</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>10. I am honest</p>\r\n<p>A. Didn&rsquo;t I?</p>\r\n<p>B. Am I?</p>\r\n<p>C. Am not I?</p>\r\n<p>D. Aren&rsquo;t I?</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>BASIC MATHEMATICS</p>\r\n<p>1.&nbsp; If 16=11, 25=12, 36=15, then 49=?</p>\r\n<p>A. 14</p>\r\n<p>B. 20</p>\r\n<p>C. 19</p>\r\n<p>D. 17</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>2. Which number is missing 1, 9, 25, 49, ?</p>\r\n<p>A. 121</p>\r\n<p>B. 81</p>\r\n<p>C. 16</p>\r\n<p>D. 169</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>3. 561204 x 58 = ? x 55555</p>\r\n<p>A. 606</p>\r\n<p>B. 646</p>\r\n<p>C. 586</p>\r\n<p>D. 716</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>4. If 6 is 50% of a number, what is the number?</p>\r\n<p>A. 10</p>\r\n<p>B. 11</p>\r\n<p>C. 12</p>\r\n<p>D. 13</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>5. Which least number should be added to 2600 to make it a perfect square?</p>\r\n<p>A. 3</p>\r\n<p>B. 39</p>\r\n<p>C. 1</p>\r\n<p>D. 5</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>6. The number which is neither prime nor composite is &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;</p>\r\n<p>A. 0</p>\r\n<p>B. 1</p>\r\n<p>C. 3</p>\r\n<p>D. 2</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>7. If &lsquo;+&rsquo; means &lsquo;x&rsquo;, &lsquo;-&lsquo; means &lsquo;+&rsquo;, &lsquo;x&rsquo; means &lsquo;\\&rsquo; and &lsquo;\\&rsquo; means &lsquo;-&lsquo; then find the value of; 6 &ndash; 9 + 8 x 3 \\ 20 = &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;</p>\r\n<p>A. 6</p>\r\n<p>B. 10</p>\r\n<p>C. -2</p>\r\n<p>D. 12</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>8. What is 121 times 11?</p>\r\n<p>A. 1331</p>\r\n<p>B. 1313</p>\r\n<p>C. 1133</p>\r\n<p>D. 3131</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>9. In the following series, a wrong number is given. Find out the number. 4, 5, 10, 18, 34, 59, 95</p>\r\n<p>A. 5</p>\r\n<p>B. 10</p>\r\n<p>C. 18</p>\r\n<p>D. 34</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>10. A number is greater than 3 but less than 8. Also the number is greater than 6 but less than 10. What is the number?</p>\r\n<p>A. 5</p>\r\n<p>B. 6</p>\r\n<p>C. 7</p>\r\n<p>D. 8</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>CORRENTS AFFAIRS</p>\r\n<p>1. Which state is referred to as &ldquo;The Gateway State&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>A. Ekiti State</p>\r\n<p>B. Ogun State</p>\r\n<p>C. Jigawa State</p>\r\n<p>D. Oyo State</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>2. Nigerian Civil War Started in what year?</p>\r\n<p>A. 1967</p>\r\n<p>B. 1970</p>\r\n<p>C. 1966</p>\r\n<p>D. 1985</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>3. Nigeria celebrated her last centenary anniversary in what year?</p>\r\n<p>A. 2000</p>\r\n<p>B. 2014</p>\r\n<p>C. 2020</p>\r\n<p>D. 1990</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>4. The state with the least number of local governments in Nigeria is &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..</p>\r\n<p>A. Zamfara</p>\r\n<p>B. Lagos</p>\r\n<p>C. Bayelsa</p>\r\n<p>D. Anambra</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>5. Which state is referred to as the sunshine state?</p>\r\n<p>A. Ekiti State</p>\r\n<p>B. Ondo State</p>\r\n<p>C. Jigawa State</p>\r\n<p>D. Oyo state</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2019-12-09 21:33:17'),
