(16, 'Last week Saturday quiz questions and answers', '<p>BASIC COMPUTER</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;1. The brain of any computer system is&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A. ALU</p>\r\n<p>B. Memory</p>\r\n<p>C. CPU</p>\r\n<p>D. CU</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>2. What difference does the 5th generation computer have from other generation computers?</p>\r\n<p>A. Technological Advancement</p>\r\n<p>B. Scientific Code</p>\r\n<p>C. Object oriented</p>\r\n<p>D. None of the above</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>3. Computer monitor is also known as:</p>\r\n<p>A. DVU</p>\r\n<p>B. UVD</p>\r\n<p>C. VDU</p>\r\n<p>D. CCTV</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>4. Arrange in ascending order the units of memory TB, KB, GB, MB.</p>\r\n<p>A. TB&gt;MB&gt;GB&gt;KB</p>\r\n<p>B. MB&gt;GB&gt;TB&gt;KB</p>\r\n<p>C. TB&gt;GB&gt;MB&gt;KB</p>\r\n<p>D. GB&gt;MB&gt;KB&gt;TB</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>5. The printed output from a computer is called</p>\r\n<p>A. copy</p>\r\n<p>B. Soft Copy</p>\r\n<p>C. Hard Copy</p>\r\n<p>D. Paper</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>6. Where is RAM located?</p>\r\n<p>A. Expansion Board</p>\r\n<p>B. External Drive</p>\r\n<p>C. Mother Board</p>\r\n<p>D. All of the above</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>7. Full form of URL is</p>\r\n<p>A. Uniform Resource Locator</p>\r\n<p>B. Uniform Resource Link</p>\r\n<p>C. Uniform Registered Link</p>\r\n<p>D. Unified Resource Link</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>8. Who was the founder of Bluetooth?</p>\r\n<p>A. Ericson</p>\r\n<p>B. Martin Cooper</p>\r\n<p>C. Steve Jobs</p>\r\n<p>D. Apple</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>9. Who was the founder of Internet?</p>\r\n<p>A. Charles Babbage</p>\r\n<p>B. Vint Cerf</p>\r\n<p>C. Denis Riche</p>\r\n<p>D. Martin Cooper.</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>10. Verification is a process of?</p>\r\n<p>A. Access</p>\r\n<p>B. Login</p>\r\n<p>C. Logout</p>\r\n<p>D. Authentication</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>ENGLISH</p>\r\n<p>1. Select correct word.</p>\r\n<p>A. Veengeance&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>B. Vengence&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>C. Vengeance&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>D. Venggeance</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>2. Select the correct word</p>\r\n<p>A. Exagerate</p>\r\n<p>B. Exegerate&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>C. Exaaggerate&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>D. Exaggerate</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>3. Select the most appropriate meaning of the given idiom &ldquo;butterflies in the stomach &rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>A. Being angry</p>\r\n<p>B. Being hungry</p>\r\n<p>C. Being excited</p>\r\n<p>D. Being nervous</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>4. Select the most appropriate word to fill in the blank &ldquo;The National war memorial is &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.to our Armed forces&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>A. Dedicated</p>\r\n<p>B. Devoted</p>\r\n<p>C. honored</p>\r\n<p>D. Inscribed</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>5. Select the word which matches same as the group of words given.</p>\r\n<p>A family of young animals</p>\r\n<p>A. Nest</p>\r\n<p>B. Brood</p>\r\n<p>C. Offspring&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>D. Clutch</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>6. Select the wrongly spelt word in the following</p>\r\n<p>A. Reminascant</p>\r\n<p>B. Remembrance&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>C. Remnant</p>\r\n<p>D. Remittance&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>7. Find correct spelling in given words</p>\r\n<p>A. Ommineous</p>\r\n<p>B. Ominous</p>\r\n<p>C. Omineous</p>\r\n<p>D. Omenous</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>8. Select the antonym of the given word</p>\r\n<p>GATHER</p>\r\n<p>A. Disperse</p>\r\n<p>B. distract</p>\r\n<p>C. dispute</p>\r\n<p>D. display</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>9. Select the wrongly spelt word</p>\r\n<p>A. Hasty</p>\r\n<p>B. Hastitate&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>C. Hazard</p>\r\n<p>D. Hazy</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>10. Select the synonym of the given word&nbsp; DRAG</p>\r\n<p>A. Rest</p>\r\n<p>B. Rush</p>\r\n<p>C. Push</p>\r\n<p>D. Pull</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>BASIC MATHEMATICS</p>\r\n<p>1.&nbsp; how many lines can be drawn through two points</p>\r\n<p>A. 1</p>\r\n<p>B. 2</p>\r\n<p>C. 3</p>\r\n<p>D. Not possible</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>2. Factors of 9 are &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.</p>\r\n<p>A. 1, 2, and 3</p>\r\n<p>B. 1, 2, 3, and 9</p>\r\n<p>C. 1, 6, and 9</p>\r\n<p>D. None of these</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>3. When we multiply an exact number by zero what will be the exact answer?</p>\r\n<p>A. The exact number</p>\r\n<p>B. Cannot be multiplied</p>\r\n<p>C. Zero</p>\r\n<p>D. None of these.</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>\r\n<p>4. How many digits answers we will get when we add 99 and 1?</p>\r\n<p>A. 1</p>\r\n<p>B. 3</p>\r\n<p>C. 99</p>\r\n<p>E. 100</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>5. What is 999 times 100.0?</p>\r\n<p>A. 199.0</p>\r\n<p>B. 999.0</p>\r\n<p>C. 9990</p>\r\n<p>D. 99900</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>6. What is the unit of volume?</p>\r\n<p>A. Square units</p>\r\n<p>B. Cubic units</p>\r\n<p>C. Only Unit</p>\r\n<p>D. None of these</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>7. 1010 gram = &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..kg</p>\r\n<p>A. 10.10kg</p>\r\n<p>B. 101.0kg</p>\r\n<p>C. 1.001kg</p>\r\n<p>D. 1.01kg</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>8. How many times is 1000 bigger than 1?</p>\r\n<p>A. 1 time</p>\r\n<p>B. 10 times</p>\r\n<p>C. 100 times</p>\r\n<p>D. 1000 times</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>9. Average of three person&rsquo;s age is 9 years. Find some of there age</p>\r\n<p>A. 18</p>\r\n<p>B. 21</p>\r\n<p>C. 24</p>\r\n<p>D. 27</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>10. Name a triangle whose two angles are equal</p>\r\n<p>A. Right angle triangle</p>\r\n<p>B. Isosceles triangle</p>\r\n<p>C. Scalene triangle</p>\r\n<p>D. None of these</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>CORRENTS AFFAIRS</p>\r\n<p>1. When was the Nigerian Naira introduced?</p>\r\n<p>A. 1st January 1973</p>\r\n<p>B. 1st May 1973</p>\r\n<p>C. 27th April 1973</p>\r\n<p>D. 8th October&nbsp; 1973&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>2. One of these is not among the registered political parties in Nigeria in 1982</p>\r\n<p>A. UPN</p>\r\n<p>B. PDP</p>\r\n<p>C. NAP</p>\r\n<p>D. NPN</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [B].</p>\r\n<p>3. Which country won the 2018 world cup?</p>\r\n<p>A. Croatia</p>\r\n<p>B. Argentina</p>\r\n<p>C. England</p>\r\n<p>D. France</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [D].</p>\r\n<p>4. On which day National press is observed every year?</p>\r\n<p>A. 16th November&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>B. 18th November</p>\r\n<p>C. 7th January</p>\r\n<p>D. 19th November</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [A].</p>\r\n<p>5. Orji Uzor Kalu was sentenced</p>\r\n<p>A. 6 years Imprisonment</p>\r\n<p>B. 14 years imprisonment</p>\r\n<p>C. 12 years imprisonment</p>\r\n<p>D. 10 years imprisonment</p>\r\n<p>CORRECT ANSWER IS [C].</p>', '2019-12-17 20:17:43'),
