(21, 'Last week quiz Questions and Answers ', '<p>GENERAL TEST</p>\r\n<p>1. Car A is running faster than B and slower than C. Car B is running faster than D. Which car is the fastest?</p>\r\n<p>A. B</p>\r\n<p>B. C</p>\r\n<p>C. A</p>\r\n<p>D. D</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: B</p>\r\n<p>2. 5 dogs and 5 donkeys are taking part in a race competition. What are the chances that dog will win the race?</p>\r\n<p>A. 50%</p>\r\n<p>B. 20%</p>\r\n<p>C. 10%</p>\r\n<p>D. None.</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>3. Choose the group in which all the words have at least one silent letters.</p>\r\n<p>A. Know, Intelligentsia, Club, and Silent.</p>\r\n<p>B. Intelligentsia, Intelligence, Letter, Comb.</p>\r\n<p>C. Knowledge, Education, Power, Hour</p>\r\n<p>D. Numb, Intelligentsia, Hour, Comb</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: D</p>\r\n<p>4. Two times of 50% of 100 is</p>\r\n<p>A. 200</p>\r\n<p>B. 100</p>\r\n<p>C. 50</p>\r\n<p>D. 250</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: B</p>\r\n<p>5. The 2nd last swimmer crossed the 2nd swimmer and got 2nd position. How many Swimmers took part in the swimming completion?</p>\r\n<p>A. 6</p>\r\n<p>B. 5</p>\r\n<p>C. 4</p>\r\n<p>D. 3</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: C</p>\r\n<p>6. What comes next in logical series? 1, 9, 36, 81, &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.</p>\r\n<p>A. 127</p>\r\n<p>B. 144</p>\r\n<p>C. 156</p>\r\n<p>D. 324</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: B</p>\r\n<p>7. Multiplication of two unknown digits is 72. Larger digit is twice greater than the smaller one. Sum of these digits is?</p>\r\n<p>A. 18</p>\r\n<p>B. 36</p>\r\n<p>C. 38</p>\r\n<p>D. 12</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>8. If your father is my father but my mother is not your mother. It means you are my</p>\r\n<p>A. Step brother</p>\r\n<p>B. Cousin</p>\r\n<p>C. Step Sister D. Both A and C</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: D</p>\r\n<p>9. In a hall, women are sitting in the 2nd last row. Men are sitting in 2nd row. Girls are sitting in the front row and remaining rows are filled with boys. What are the minimum number of rows in the hall?</p>\r\n<p>A. 7</p>\r\n<p>B. 6</p>\r\n<p>C. 5</p>\r\n<p>D. 4</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: D</p>\r\n<p>10. Average of A, B, and C is equal to D. Average of A, B, C and D will be equal to&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A. D</p>\r\n<p>B. 2D</p>\r\n<p>C. D/2</p>\r\n<p>D. Uncertain</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>11. If ABCDE&hellip;Z = 12345&hellip;26. Then B x O x Y (BOY) = ?</p>\r\n<p>A. 750</p>\r\n<p>B. 42</p>\r\n<p>C. 21525</p>\r\n<p>D. All</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>12. Average of A and B is 2 times greater than average of C and D. Sum of C and D will be equal to&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A. A+B</p>\r\n<p>B. 2A+2B</p>\r\n<p>C. 2(A+B)</p>\r\n<p>D. (A+B)/2</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: D</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>IQ TEST</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>1. Sam is 11 years old. Ross is twice as old as Sam. When Ross is 50years old, how old will Sam be?</p>\r\n<p>A. 39</p>\r\n<p>B. 41</p>\r\n<p>C. 43</p>\r\n<p>D. 38</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>2. Jack and John have 56 marbles together. John has 6x more marbles than jack. How many marbles does jack have?</p>\r\n<p>A. 10</p>\r\n<p>B. 8</p>\r\n<p>C. 50</p>\r\n<p>D. 45</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: B</p>\r\n<p>3. Round 4.846 to the nearest tenth</p>\r\n<p>A. 4.9</p>\r\n<p>B. 4.87</p>\r\n<p>C. 5</p>\r\n<p>D. 4.7</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>4. Identify the next number in the series. 15, 225, 9, 81, 3, &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.</p>\r\n<p>A. -3</p>\r\n<p>B. 12</p>\r\n<p>C. 1</p>\r\n<p>D. 9</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: D</p>\r\n<p>5. The cost of one paper is 15 Cents. How much will 40 papers cost?</p>\r\n<p>A. $40.00</p>\r\n<p>B. $6.00</p>\r\n<p>C. $2.60</p>\r\n<p>D. $4.00</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: B</p>\r\n<p>6. The opposite of daunting is</p>\r\n<p>A. hard</p>\r\n<p>B. Severe</p>\r\n<p>C. tired</p>\r\n<p>D. Simple</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: D</p>\r\n<p>7. A car travels 5feet in 0.5seconds. How far will it go in a minuite?</p>\r\n<p>A. 600feet</p>\r\n<p>B. 500feet</p>\r\n<p>C. 150feet</p>\r\n<p>D. 900feet</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>8. What do you get when you add 12 + 1.009 + 2.11 + 3.001?</p>\r\n<p>A. 18.12</p>\r\n<p>B. 19.01</p>\r\n<p>C. 19.112</p>\r\n<p>D. 18.21</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>9. Arrange these words to form a sentence. The sentence you arranged, is it true or false? Triangle sides a has three</p>\r\n<p>A. True</p>\r\n<p>B. false</p>\r\n<p>C. Correct answer not available</p>\r\n<p>D. A triangle has three sides.</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>10. What will you get if you reduce 14/35 to the lowest term?</p>\r\n<p>A. 2/5</p>\r\n<p>B. 3/5</p>\r\n<p>C. 1/5</p>\r\n<p>D. 7/10</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>11. What does FAQ?</p>\r\n<p>A. Fast asked question</p>\r\n<p>B. Frequently asked questions</p>\r\n<p>C. Frequently asked queries</p>\r\n<p>D. Frequently answered questions.</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: B</p>\r\n<p>12. How many Seconds are there in a day?</p>\r\n<p>A. 86,400</p>\r\n<p>B. 82,400</p>\r\n<p>C. 88,400</p>\r\n<p>D. 85,400</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>13. Find the average of 14, 17, 22, 27</p>\r\n<p>A. 18</p>\r\n<p>B. 27</p>\r\n<p>C. 15</p>\r\n<p>D. 20</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: D</p>\r\n<p>14. Akin and Comparable have &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. Meanings?</p>\r\n<p>A. opposite</p>\r\n<p>B. Unrelated</p>\r\n<p>C. Contradicting&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>D. Similar</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: D</p>\r\n<p>15. Reduce and Produce have &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. Meanings?</p>\r\n<p>A. opposite</p>\r\n<p>B. similar</p>\r\n<p>C. neither similar nor opposite</p>\r\n<p>D. None of these</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>16. Identify the number in the sequence. 41, 29, 35, 23,&nbsp; &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..</p>\r\n<p>A. 22</p>\r\n<p>B. 24</p>\r\n<p>C. 21</p>\r\n<p>D. 29</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: D</p>\r\n<p>17. Which one of the five is least like the other three?</p>\r\n<p>A. Billiards</p>\r\n<p>B. Badminton</p>\r\n<p>C. Golf</p>\r\n<p>D. football</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: D</p>\r\n<p>18. OCEAN is to AENCO as 89653 is to:</p>\r\n<p>A. 85369 B. 56389</p>\r\n<p>C. 56398</p>\r\n<p>D. 65398</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: C</p>\r\n<p>19. If you rearrange the letter &ldquo;RANDIEMAN&rdquo; you&rsquo;d have the name of a:</p>\r\n<p>A. City</p>\r\n<p>B. Novel</p>\r\n<p>C. Country D. Fruit.</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: D</p>\r\n<p>20. Virus is to Vaccine as exam is to:</p>\r\n<p>A. attempting</p>\r\n<p>B. failing</p>\r\n<p>C. Studying&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>D. Passing</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: C</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2020-01-14 08:50:35'),
