(23, 'Last week quiz Questions and Answers ', '<p>GENERAL TEST</p>\r\n<p>1. A man pointing to a photograph says. &ldquo;The lady in the photograph is my nephew&rsquo;s maternal grandmother.&rdquo; How is the lady in the photograph related to the man&rsquo;s sister who has no other sister?</p>\r\n<p>A. Mother-in-law</p>\r\n<p>B. Cousin</p>\r\n<p>C. Sister-in-law</p>\r\n<p>D. Mother</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: D</p>\r\n<p>2. A and B are young ones of C. If C is the father of A but B is not the son of C. How are B and C related?</p>\r\n<p>A. Niece and Uncle</p>\r\n<p>B. Daughter and father</p>\r\n<p>C. Niece and Uncle</p>\r\n<p>D. Daughter and Mother</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: B</p>\r\n<p>3. A woman introduces a man as the son of the brother of her mother. How is the man related to the woman?</p>\r\n<p>A. Uncle</p>\r\n<p>B. Grandson</p>\r\n<p>C. Cousin</p>\r\n<p>D. Son</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: C</p>\r\n<p>4. Find the odd one out</p>\r\n<p>A. Flourish</p>\r\n<p>B. Renovate</p>\r\n<p>C. Blossom</p>\r\n<p>D. Thrive</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: B</p>\r\n<p>5. Find the odd one out</p>\r\n<p>A. Vapour</p>\r\n<p>B. Mist</p>\r\n<p>C. Hailstone</p>\r\n<p>D. Fog</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>6. If ABCDE&hellip;Z = 12345&hellip;26. Then B x O x Y (BOY) =?</p>\r\n<p>A. 750</p>\r\n<p>B. 42</p>\r\n<p>C. 21525</p>\r\n<p>D. All</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>7. A car travels 5feet in 0.5seconds. How far will it go in a minute?</p>\r\n<p>A. 600feet</p>\r\n<p>B. 500feet</p>\r\n<p>C. 150feet</p>\r\n<p>D. 900feet</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>8. Which word has a meaning most opposite of the word DISGUST?</p>\r\n<p>A. Fatuation</p>\r\n<p>B. Love</p>\r\n<p>C. Attract</p>\r\n<p>D. Lust</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: C</p>\r\n<p>9. What is 20% of 60?</p>\r\n<p>A. 17</p>\r\n<p>B. 12</p>\r\n<p>C. 14</p>\r\n<p>D. 15</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: B</p>\r\n<p>10. What is the average of 12, 15, 23, and 22?</p>\r\n<p>A. 20</p>\r\n<p>B. 16</p>\r\n<p>C. 18</p>\r\n<p>D. 15</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: C</p>\r\n<p>11. The opposite of conclusion is?</p>\r\n<p>A. Exclusion</p>\r\n<p>B. Inclusion</p>\r\n<p>C. Beginning</p>\r\n<p>D. Ending</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: C</p>\r\n<p>12. -43+9 =?</p>\r\n<p>A. -34</p>\r\n<p>B. -32</p>\r\n<p>C. 32</p>\r\n<p>D. 34</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>13. (8/4) x (9/3) =?</p>\r\n<p>A. 12</p>\r\n<p>B. 15</p>\r\n<p>C. 10</p>\r\n<p>D. 6</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: D</p>\r\n<p>14. Kelvin is 21 years old and his sister is third his age. When kelvin is 36, what will be the age of his sister?</p>\r\n<p>A. 24</p>\r\n<p>B. 36</p>\r\n<p>C. 28</p>\r\n<p>D. 22</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: D</p>\r\n<p>15. Which of the month has 28 days?</p>\r\n<p>A. February</p>\r\n<p>B. January</p>\r\n<p>C. 12 Months</p>\r\n<p>D. None of the Months</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: C</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>CURRENT AFFAIRS</p>\r\n<p>1. A nation consists of people with</p>\r\n<p>A. Common ancestry</p>\r\n<p>B. Common history</p>\r\n<p>C. A shared set of values</p>\r\n<p>D. All of the above.</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: D</p>\r\n<p>2. One of these was in existence before the outbreak of the Second World War</p>\r\n<p>A. The UNO</p>\r\n<p>B. The OAU</p>\r\n<p>C. The League of Nations</p>\r\n<p>D. Common wealth of Nations</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: C</p>\r\n<p>3. Herbert Macaulay was the first President of&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A. NEPU</p>\r\n<p>B. NCNC</p>\r\n<p>C. UMBC</p>\r\n<p>D. AG</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: B</p>\r\n<p>4. Fascism originated from</p>\r\n<p>A. Greece</p>\r\n<p>B. Italy</p>\r\n<p>C. China</p>\r\n<p>D. Germany</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: B</p>\r\n<p>5. Democracy was first practiced in&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A. Greece</p>\r\n<p>B. Ghana</p>\r\n<p>C. Britain</p>\r\n<p>D. USA</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>BASIC COMPUTER</p>\r\n<p>1. Which of the following companies developed MS office</p>\r\n<p>A. Microsoft</p>\r\n<p>B. Novell</p>\r\n<p>C. Corel</p>\r\n<p>D. Lotus</p>\r\n<p>Correct Answer: A</p>\r\n<p>2. MS word allows creation of &hellip;&hel